#: ../../A/alt.rst:5
msgid "alt"
msgstr "alt"

#: ../../A/alt.rst:7
msgid "/awlt/"
msgstr "/awlt/"

#: ../../A/alt.rst:9
msgid ""
"n\\. The alt shift key on an IBM PC or :ref:`clone` keyboard; see "
":ref:`bucky-bits`\\, sense 2 (though typical PC usage does not simply set "
"the 0200 bit)."
msgstr ""
"名詞。IBM PCや\\ :ref:`clone`\\ のキーボードにあるaltシフトキー。\\ :ref:`bucky-bits`\\ "
"の語義2を参照(ただし通常のPCの用法は単に0200ビットを立てるわけではない)。"

#: ../../A/alt.rst:12
msgid ""
"n\\. The option key on a Macintosh; use of this term usually reveals that "
"the speaker hacked PCs before coming to the Mac (see also :ref:`feature-"
"key`\\, which is sometimes *incorrectly* called ‘alt’)."
msgstr ""
"名詞。Macintoshのoptionキー。この用語を使うと、たいてい話者がMacに来る前にPCをいじっていたことが露見する(\\ "
":ref:`feature-key`\\ も参照。これは時々\\ *誤って*\\ ‘alt’と呼ばれる)。"

#: ../../A/alt.rst:16
msgid ""
"The :samp:`alt` hierarchy on Usenet, the tree of newsgroups created by users"
" without a formal vote and approval procedure. There is a myth, not entirely"
" implausible, that :samp:`alt` is acronymic for \"anarchists, lunatics, and "
"terrorists\"; but in fact it is simply short for \"alternative\"."
msgstr ""
"Usenet上の\\ :samp:`alt`\\ 階層、すなわち正式な投票・承認手続きを経ずにユーザーが作成したニュースグループの木。\\ "
":samp:`alt`\\ は「anarchists, lunatics, and "
"terrorists(無政府主義者、狂人、テロリスト)」の頭字語だ、というあながち荒唐無稽でもない俗説があるが、実際には単に「alternative(代替)」の略にすぎない。"

#: ../../A/alt.rst:19
msgid ""
"n.,obs. Rare alternate name for the ASCII ESC character (ASCII 0011011). "
"This use, derives, with the alt key itself, from archaic PDP-10 operating "
"systems, especially :ref:`ITS`\\."
msgstr ""
"名詞、廃語。ASCII ESC文字(ASCII "
"0011011)のまれな別名。この用法は、altキー自体とともに、旧式のPDP-10オペレーティングシステム、特に\\ :ref:`ITS`\\ "
"に由来する。"
